column5: Hi all,  With jack at school in the mornings i sneak off for regular, although shorter, fishing trips. Went down to Williams Bay on Lac Seul this morning and got to test out my 'new to me ' fish finder', works pretty good.  Time was a major factor in my success rate today. Although i caught a nice mixed bag of species, the usual walleye tally was way down, I did not have time to head up the lake and I had in my mind that if I ran into issues there were no other boats around, cant say I would be too bothered about spending a couple of days on an island waiting for pick up(i go prepared) but Jack would not be impressed when nobody showed to pick him up  .  Here is a video from my morning.
Very nice! It must suck having Lac Seul on your doorstep. It's Hamilton Harbor for me once I get the kids off to school LOL!
That sure got my fishing blood going, Simon. Your 16 is nice and clean. Do you know why your GPS isn't working?
Great video !!!!! was there on Labor day weekend ,,,that is my all time favorite lake..the walleye there are so golden...quite the drive in thou lol

Always enjoy your videos and updates from God's country.  I watched this video recently and for whatever reason it reminded me of you (although, I know you're not Australian one of the guys kind of sounds like you).  http://youtu.be/Syxqhgzi0UA
Really enjoyed  this video! Lac Seul on you doorstep must be nice.
Living the life there Simon... another great video! Thanks for posting and don't tell Jack you got out fishing! HH
Really enjoyed  this video! Lac Seul on you doorstep must be nice.  x2
